  "extraHighlightWords": [
    {
      "word": "episode",
      "pos": "n.",
      "zh": "一集；事件",
      "phonetic": "",
      "level": "extra",
      "firstOccurrenceSentenceIndex": 10,
      "highlightType": "extra-high-frequency"
    }
  ],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Mei's family lived in a small apartment with her parents and her younger brother, all sharing one bedroom.",
      "zh": "Mei 的家人住在一間小公寓裡，跟爸媽和弟弟一起，全家共用一間臥室。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She hoped that if she practiced hard enough, her dream of joining a real music school might come true one day.",
      "zh": "她希望只要練習得夠努力，有一天加入正式音樂學校的夢想真的能實現。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mei sat back down, her guitar across her knees, and did not look at them for a moment.",
      "zh": "Mei 又坐了下來，吉他橫放在膝蓋上，有那麼一刻沒有看他們。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"It's not really a secret,\" she said finally. \"It's just... not official, either.\"",
      "zh": "她最後說：「這其實不算秘密，只是⋯⋯也不算正式。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "She explained that she wanted to join the school's music show next month.",
      "zh": "她解釋說，她想參加下個月的學校音樂表演。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"The band room is always full,\" she said. \"And there's no space at home to practice.\"",
      "zh": "她說：「音樂教室永遠都是滿的，家裡也沒有空間可以練習。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "A few weeks ago, she asked a teacher if she could use an empty classroom after school.",
      "zh": "幾星期前，她問了一位老師，能不能借用一間放學後空著的教室。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"The teacher said yes, if the room was empty,\" Mei said. \"But I don't think anyone else was told.\"",
      "zh": "Mei 說：「老師說可以，只要教室是空的，但我覺得沒有人告訴其他人這件事。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "So every day, she checked if Room 306 was free, and quietly let herself in.",
      "zh": "所以她每天都會確認306教室有沒有空，然後悄悄地進去。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"I didn't want to ask again,\" she said. \"I was scared the answer might change.\"",
      "zh": "她說：「我不想再問一次，我怕答案會變。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice's eyes lit up. \"This would make a great episode.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 眼睛一亮：「這會是很棒的一集。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco gave her a look. \"We ask first,\" she said. \"Remember?\"",
      "zh": "Coco 看了她一眼：「我們要先問過，」她說：「記得嗎？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice turned to Mei. \"Would you want your story on the show? Only if you say yes.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 轉向 Mei：「你希望你的故事上節目嗎？只有你說好才算。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mei thought about it for a long moment. \"Not my name,\" she said. \"But... maybe the idea.\"",
      "zh": "Mei 想了好一會兒：「不要說我的名字，」她說：「但⋯⋯也許可以講這個想法。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"What idea?\" Coco asked.",
      "zh": "Coco 問：「什麼想法？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"That students need real practice space,\" Mei said. \"Not just borrowed rooms that could disappear any day.\"",
      "zh": "Mei 說：「學生需要真正的練習空間，不是隨時可能消失的借來的房間。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "That sentence stayed with Coco long after they left Room 306.",
      "zh": "這句話在他們離開306教室後，一直留在 Coco 心裡。"
    },
    {
      "en": "That evening, she brought the whole story to Mr. Pan, careful to leave Mei's name out of it.",
      "zh": "那天晚上，她把整件事告訴潘老師，小心地沒有提到 Mei 的名字。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan listened, then asked one simple question. \"What does she actually want us to do?\"",
      "zh": "潘老師聽完，問了一個簡單的問題：「她真正希望我們做什麼？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"She wants the room to be official,\" Coco said. \"Not a secret anyone could take away.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 說：「她希望這個房間變成正式的，而不是隨時可能被拿走的秘密。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Then that's the episode,\" Mr. Pan said. \"Not about one girl. About a real problem worth fixing.\"",
      "zh": "潘老師說：「那就是這一集的重點，不是關於一個女生，而是關於一個值得解決的真正問題。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco wrote down the new plan, feeling, for the first time in this case, that they finally knew what to do.",
      "zh": "Coco 寫下新計畫，這是這個案子裡，她第一次覺得他們終於知道該怎麼做了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mei's father worked as a driver, and her mother sewed clothes for a small shop near their apartment.",
      "zh": "Mei 的爸爸是司機，媽媽在他們公寓附近的一間小商店幫忙縫製衣服。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Her little brother was still a baby, and the whole family often stayed up late just to keep him calm.",
      "zh": "她的弟弟還是個嬰兒，全家人常常熬夜就為了讓他保持安靜。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mei's music teacher once told her that talent alone was never enough without daily practice.",
      "zh": "Mei 的音樂老師曾告訴她，光有天分不夠，還是需要每天練習。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"I'm not the smartest player in my class,\" Mei admitted, \"but I'm probably the most stubborn one.\"",
      "zh": "Mei 坦承：「我不是班上彈得最好的人，但我大概是最固執的一個。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "That week, Mei's family had a video call with a relative who had moved abroad years ago.",
      "zh": "那個星期，Mei 家跟一位多年前搬到國外的親戚視訊通話。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Her relative said the national news abroad barely mentioned their small hometown at all.",
      "zh": "那位親戚說，國外的國家新聞幾乎完全沒提過他們的小家鄉。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"I still miss it,\" the relative said, \"even the noise, even the busy streets.\"",
      "zh": "親戚說：「我還是很想念，連那些吵鬧、連那些擁擠的街道都想念。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mei's mother recorded the whole call, saying it was worth keeping for years to come.",
      "zh": "Mei 的媽媽把整通通話錄了下來，說這值得留存好幾年。"
    }
  ],
  "quiz": [
